<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Adansonia ser. 2, 14 (2): 273" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="Engl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Ledermanniella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ledermanniella aloides" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ledermanniella aloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been assessed globally as Vulnerable by 
<bibRefCitation author="Diop, FN" journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B22" refString="Diop, FN, 2010a. Ledermanniellaaloides. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185425A8409077. [Downloaded on 14 August 2018]" title="Ledermanniellaaloides. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185425 A 8409077. [Downloaded on 14 August 2018]" year="2010 a">Diop (2010a)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
assessed this taxon for Cameroon as Endangered. The taxon is known from one locality. The extent of occurrence, and the area of occupancy are both estimated at 4 km2 each. Based on the area of occupancy, the number of localities and the agricultural development impact in the area, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="L. aloides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">L. aloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reassessed and maintained as Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered EN B2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
